author: Noah Higgins-Dunn
title: Two pet cats in New York test positive for the coronavirus, CDC says
description: The two cats live in separate areas of the state and are expected to make a full recovery, the CDC said in a statement.
content:
The coronavirus has infected two cats in New York state, making them the first pets to test positive for the virus in the U.S., the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention said on Wednesday.
